cs.SE, cs.IR, cs.PL, cs.HC, cs.CY. 

The paper focuses on developing an IDE-based web search solution for software developers to search for information related to programming errors and exceptions. This involves capturing content-relevance, context-relevance, popularity, and search engine confidence of each candidate result against encountered programming problems. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Software Engineering (cs.SE) as it deals with software development and maintenance. Additionally, the paper also involves Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as it proposes a meta search engine that captures various relevance factors of search results. The paper also involves Programming Languages (cs.PL) as it deals with programming errors and exceptions. Furthermore, the paper also involves Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) as it aims to reduce the time-consuming and distracting frequent switching between web browser and IDE. Finally, the paper also involves Cybersecurity (cs.CY) as it deals with identifying and resolving programming errors and exceptions, which can be potential security vulnerabilities.
